reviewText:
pros: Simpatia e disponibilidade dos funcionários;
Localização (a poucos metros da praia e da marina);
Spa e Piscinas;
Conforto do quarto e limpeza;
Pequeno almoço bom e variado. cons: O único ponto fraco do resort são os restaurantes. O serviço de buffet tem alguma variedade mas a qualidade dos pratos é fraca (mas está dentro do que se espera neste tipo de serviço). No restaurante à carta os pratos têm ideias interessantes mas a confecção e a qualidade dos produtos é bastante fraca. A carta de vinhos é bastante limitada nos dois restaurantes.

pros: great property; great services; very professional staff; stylish environment; cons: poor communication with reservations team (we were given wrong information; very misleading);
did the enquiry before booking about the swimming pool facilities for the kids where we were informed that “kids can use indoor pool”; however on arrival there was unpleasant surprise - kids are allowed to the indoor pool only 10am-12pm (2 hours only) and the rest of the day you are left without the possibility to use that indoor pool; 

if we were informed about it before booking that wouldn’t be a problem; but we asked specifically for the kids possibility to use the pool (as the outdoor pool is freezing)

very disappointing as the rest of the hotel was fantastic

pros: The resort has potential friendly staff and it's fresh (less than year and a half) but they have to improve many things. For now quite far away from "world-class service" but appreciate the attention from the general manager. He's very polite with the right mindset. 
If you want a high-quality resort in the south of Portugal I do recommend checking out some other options: 
- Herdade da Malhadinha Nova - Relais & Châteaux (stylish winery & resort);
- Octant Vila Monte (more like a very nice & cozy countryside resort); cons: - The road is awful. No the one is awful the second one is even worse. No way for sport or expensive cars. The management is working on it but not it's how it's;
+- There was some delay during the check-in. As far as I understand there was some error between booking.com and their software so the manager didn't see our reservation despite it being 100% prepaid. Luckily there were plenty of vacant rooms but during the high season it could be a problem. The property provided a complimentary bottle of wine as apologies for the inconvenience; 
- There is no transfer to the area/city nearby taxi services (uber bolt mytaxi) also don't work. So the only way to get in/out is to use your own car (keep in mind the road) or book some transfer very in advance; 
- There is only one restaurant and you have to make a reservation in advance. Nobody told us about that during the long check-in. If you come without reservation or earlier the staff isn't allowed to serve you a table because "they have limited capacity to provide the highest service" even if the restaurant occupancy rate is less than 40%. It took around 20 minutes to negotiate with the administrator to find a compromised option - wait half an hour with drinks and then get the menu half hour earlier for our reservation. But the restaurant staff and especially the sommelier are extremely nice and friendly no complaints. The food was ok nothing special;
- Last but not least the fire alarm was turned on at night around 2 or 3 am for a few minutes then turned off. So it was quite stressful and NOBODY say anything even during breakfast or the checkout process. Even a word. I can't understand the approach since the night sleep was ruined.

